<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.IModuleHandle.Delete" Title="Delete method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IModuleHandle">IModuleHandle</PageRef> ->
    Delete
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>Delete</TypeRef> method destroys the module handle object and releases its owning reference to the loaded module.
    </Paragraph>
    <Note Type="Important">
      <Paragraph>
        Module handles are normally stored in <TypeRef>IModuleHandle::unique_ptr</TypeRef> and destroyed by the smart pointer deleter.
      </Paragraph>
    </Note>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[void Delete() = 0;]]></Code>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="See also">
    <PageRefList>
      <PageRefListEntry PageName="cobalt.graphics.IModuleHandle">IModuleHandle</PageRefListEntry>
    </PageRefList>
  </Section>
</XMLDocContent>
